    "buildCommand": null,
    "testCommand": "gh pr create --title \"feat: secure session — token auth, encrypted transport, v1.0.0\" --body \"$(cat <<'EOF'\n## Summary\n\n- Server validates `RISUS_TOKEN` on every WebSocket connection; absent/wrong token closes with code 4401 after a uniform 3 s delay (no timing oracle)\n- Client appends `?token=` to URI, catches 4401, raises `AuthError`, re-prompts interactively\n- Token persisted in `risus.cfg` after successful connect; `--token` CLI arg overrides stored value\n- Scheme detection: `host:port` → `ws://`, bare hostname → `wss://` (TLS)\n- `load_battle()` URL fix: replace `wss://` before `ws://` (no double-replace bug)\n- `docker-compose.yml` binds server to `127.0.0.1`; Caddy TLS reverse proxy added (production profile)\n- Version bumped to 1.0.0\n- CONTRIBUTING.md: setup section, RISUS_TOKEN docs, Hetzner deployment guide\n\n## Hand-off checklist\n\n- [x] `pytest tests/unit -q` — 77 passed\n- [x] `PATH=$PWD/.venv/bin:$PATH CONTAINER_ENGINE=podman RISUS_TOKEN=test-token-for-e2e pytest tests/e2e -m e2e -q` — 11 passed\n- [x] `curl -fsS http://localhost:8765/healthz` returns `{\"ok\":true}`\n- [x] Two clients (VM + macOS via SSH tunnel) connected simultaneously, saw same state, lock indicator worked, lock denial worked\n- [x] Wrong token rejected with re-prompt; correct token connects\n\n## Merge note\n\n**Please squash-merge** — earlier commits on this branch contain a personal domain in spec/test files that has since been replaced. Squash merge drops that history.\n\n🤖 Generated with [Claude Code](https://claude.com/claude-code)\nEOF\n)\" --base main 2>&1",
